{"id":177,"date":"2021-01-06T10:59:49","date_gmt":"2021-01-06T10:59:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=177"},"modified":"2021-01-23T14:40:46","modified_gmt":"2021-01-23T14:40:46","slug":"how-to-change-raspberry-pis-hostname-password","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=177","title":{"rendered":"How to Change Raspberry PI&#8217;s Hostname \/ Password"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>By default your Raspberry PI&#8217;s hostname is <strong>raspberrypi<\/strong> and your password is <strong>raspberry<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There is nothing wrong with this name until you have multiple PIes in your network and trust me when you buy one, you will want more of them to do even more cool projects. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So in this short guide I&#8217;ll show you how to change the hostname and the password.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We can choose multiple paths to do so. In this guide I&#8217;ll show you one way over <strong>CLI<\/strong> (console) and one way over <strong>GUI<\/strong> (graphical interface)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Changing Hostname \/ Password Using CLI<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Because our PI is running Raspbian we can use one of it&#8217;s features that is called <strong>raspi-config<\/strong> which allow us to change these things with very friendly user interface.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Connect<\/strong> and <strong>login<\/strong> to your PI, you can find how in this <a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=136\">guide<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the console type:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>sudo raspi-config <\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>You should see option menu like this. Choose the <strong>System option<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"374\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-14.png?resize=640%2C374&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-180\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-14.png?w=867&amp;ssl=1 867w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-14.png?resize=300%2C175&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-14.png?resize=768%2C449&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Select the <strong>S4 Hostname<\/strong> and choose a new hostname. Keep in mind that you can only use <strong>ASCII<\/strong> letters <strong>a-z<\/strong>, the digits <strong>0-9<\/strong> and the <strong>hyphen<\/strong>, but hostname cannot begin nor end with hyphen.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"378\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-15.png?resize=640%2C378&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-181\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-15.png?w=868&amp;ssl=1 868w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-15.png?resize=300%2C177&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-15.png?resize=768%2C453&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Congratulation, now do the same for the password and you will be send into a terminal in which you will type your new password.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"377\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-17.png?resize=640%2C377&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-183\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-17.png?w=864&amp;ssl=1 864w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-17.png?resize=300%2C177&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-17.png?resize=768%2C452&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"81\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-16.png?resize=640%2C81&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-182\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-16.png?w=866&amp;ssl=1 866w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-16.png?resize=300%2C38&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-16.png?resize=768%2C98&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep in mind that you need to reboot your device before hostname changes will take a place. For reboot just type:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo shutdown -r +0<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Changing Hostname \/ Password Using GUI<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p> If you have installed <strong>Raspberry PI OS with desktop<\/strong> and you are more used to work with graphical intreface, this is even easier method of changing the hostname or password. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>First you need to connect your monitor or launch VNC to connect to the PI with ahernet cable. You can find guide for that <a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=136\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the left upper corner select <strong>Raspbian Icon<\/strong> and select <strong>Prefrences&gt;Raspberry Pi Configuration<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"474\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-19.png?resize=640%2C474&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-186\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-19.png?w=1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-19.png?resize=300%2C222&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-19.png?resize=768%2C569&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You should see an option to change hostname and password. Click into the window where it says <strong>raspberrypi<\/strong> and rename it to whatever you want. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then click on <strong>Change Password<\/strong> and pick your new password.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"603\" height=\"464\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-20.png?resize=603%2C464&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-187\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-20.png?w=603&amp;ssl=1 603w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/image-20.png?resize=300%2C231&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 603px) 100vw, 603px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Congratulation, you have successfully changed your hostname and password. Now you dont have worry about logging into a wrong PI or about somebody logging into yours!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>By default your Raspberry PI&#8217;s hostname is raspberrypi and your password is raspberry. There is [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":198,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[96],"tags":[98,100,102,104,106,108,110,112,114,116],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/template.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/177"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=177"}],"version-history":[{"count":4,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/177\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":190,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/177\/revisions\/190"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/198"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fmedia&parent=177"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcategories&post=177"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Ftags&post=177"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}